description:
As of March 5, 2020, Malaysian government banned its citizens from visiting these regions:
- Lombardy, Veneto and Emilia-Romagna, Italy;
- Hokkaido, Japan;
- Tehran, Qom and Gilan, Iran
Additionally, they restricted residents of above-mentioned regions to enter Malaysia.

On 16th of March (2020), Malaysian government announced MCO [Movement Control Order]: since 18th of March

1)  restricts movement and assembly nationwide;

2)  restricts travel for all Malaysians going overseas;

3)  restricts foreign visitors and tourists into Malaysia;

UPDATE: This MCO was extended until April 14, 2020, decided on March 25

UPDATE: This MCO was extended until May 12, 2020.

